        Divide each element of this set by the monomial ``rhs`` and
        return a new set containing the result.

        EXAMPLE::

            sage: B.<a,b,c,d,e,f> = BooleanPolynomialRing(order='lex')
            sage: f = b*e + b*c*d + b
            sage: s = f.set(); s
            {{b,c,d}, {b,e}, {b}}
